1. The Fourth Industrial Revolution is:
Ans : B. Transforming the way humans live, work, and relate to one another

2. Key drivers of the Fourth Industrial Revolution include:
Ans : C. Increased computing power, connected devices, and artificial intelligence

3. How does the scope of the Fourth Industrial Revolution differ from that of the first three?
Ans : A and C
      A. It will be more widespread because technology is more pervasive and sophisticated. 
      C. It will be more widespread because the world is so much more connected.
